      <h2>Who we are</h2>
      <p><strong>DLSU-PUSA (Professors for the Upliftment of Society's Animals)</strong> is the org that cares mainly for the Manila campus' cats—feeding, neutering/spaying to control the cat population, vaccination/antirabies shots, medical care, adopting/rehoming of stray cats & occasionally even stray dogs, etc.</p>
      <p>It has five core members, and several faculty, senior high school/undergraduate/masteral/doctoral student, and alumni volunteers and PUSApporters. PUSA is under the Office of the Vice President for Lasallian Mission.</p>
      <p>DLSU has guidelines on animals on campus approved in the Chancellor's Council, consistent with Laudato Si and the university's advocacy on the environment, & cultivation of compassion & responsibility for other species who share this planet with humans.</p>
